function.name: Thread
function.description: Creates a thread, optionaly you can specify the function to run

function.name: start
function.description:
Starts the Thread
# start(); Starts the Thread now
# start(10); Starts the Thread in 10 milseconds
# start(10,true); Executes the Thread all 10 mileseconds until you # stop(); it

parameter.name: [interval]
parameter.description: The milliseconds to wait to execute it, default=0 Execute now

parameter.name: [periodical]
parameter.description: If true the Thread will be executed repeat with the interval

function.name: stop
function.description: Stop the Thread

function.name: pause
function.description:
Pauses or unpauses the thread ( only for periodical threads )
If you want to specify if you want to pause or unpause instehead of toggle set it on paramater
It starts the thread if its not running
pause(); //Toggles from pause to unpaused pause(1); //Pause the thread pause(0); //Unpause the thread

function.name: Extends
function.description:
!!Attention!!
This function is applied to class functions not methods
Extends this from other class
must be called right after constructor
function A() { }
A.prototype.name="A";
A.prototype.test=function() {
alert(this.name);
};
function B() { }
B.Extends(A);
B.prototype.name="B";

var a= new A(), b= new B();
a.test();//alerts "A"
b.test();//alerts "B"

function.name: Implements
function.description:
!!Attention!!
This function is applied to class functions not methods
Implements an Object into this class prototype (Class.prototype)
If toStatic is true, it will implement to the class (Class)
function A() { }
A.Implements( { foo:"bar" }); A.Implements( { foo:"bar" },true); alert((new A()).foo);//bar alert(A.foo);//bar
